4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, it is unlawful for a person
6 to knowingly possess with intent to distribute obscene
7 material.
8 This bill would provide that a person who is
9 knowingly in actual or constructive possession of at
10 least 50 items or digital files containing obscene
11 material is guilty of knowingly possessing with intent
12 to distribute obscene material.
13
14
15 A BILL
16 TO BE ENTITLED
17 AN ACT
18
19 Relating to crimes and offenses; to further provide for
20 the crime of possession with intent to distribute obscene
21 material.
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
23 Section 1. Section 13A-12-200.2, Code of Alabama 1975,
24 is amended to read as follows:
25 "§13A-12-200.2
26 (a)(1) It shall be unlawful for any person to knowingly
27 distribute, possess with intent to distribute, or offer or
28 agree to distribute any obscene material or any device
